Below is a simple Julia function that meets your requirements:

```julia
abstract type Vehicle end  # abstract parent class

struct Car <: Vehicle end;
struct Motorcycle <: Vehicle end;
struct Bus <: Vehicle end;
struct Truck <: Vehicle end;

ispersonal(vehicle::Car) = true;
ispersonal(vehicle::Motorcycle) = true;
ispersonal(vehicle::Bus) = false;
ispersonal(vehicle::Truck) = false;
ispersonal(vehicle::Vehicle) = false;  # Default case: not a car or motorcycle, so isPersonal should return `false`.
```

And an example of how you could test this function would be:

```julia
println(ispersonal(Car()))    # Should print true
println(ispersonal(Motorcycle()))  # Should print true
println(ispersonal(Bus()))     # Should print false
println(ispersonal(Truck()))   # Should print false
```
